# Empty-scope rule (TARGET_ARCHITECTURE §5.4):
#   `<<scope-suffix?>>` is a conditional placeholder:
#     - At root scope (scope: ""), `<<scope-suffix?>>` expands to `` (empty string).
#     - At non-empty scope (e.g. scope: "app-checkout"), expands to `-app-checkout`.
#   Concretely:
#     Per-case id:      `TC<<scope-suffix?>>-NNN`         → `TC-001`               at root  /  `TC-app-checkout-001` at branch
#     Dotted-path ref:  `ARCH<<scope-suffix?>>.interfaces.X`
#                                                         → `ARCH.interfaces.X`   at root  /  `ARCH-app-checkout.interfaces.X` at branch
#     Dotted-path ref:  `ARCH<<scope-suffix?>>.composition.X`
#                                                         → `ARCH.composition.X`  at root  /  `ARCH-app-checkout.composition.X` at branch
#   Never emit `TC--001`, `ARCH-.interfaces.X`, or `ARCH-.composition.X`.
#
# Branch case (level: integration) — fixtures-rich shape
# Use for cases at non-leaf scope where the parent spec is an Architecture.
# Cases drive composition through published interfaces; observe cross-child state.

- id: TC<<scope-suffix?>>-NNN
  title: "<<scenario describing cross-child interaction>>"
  type: <<functional | error | fault-injection | contract | state-transition | property | performance | security | accessibility>>
  verifies:
    - "ARCH<<scope-suffix?>>.interfaces.<<name>>"        # interface contract
    # OR
    - "ARCH<<scope-suffix?>>.composition.<<invariant>>"  # composition invariant
    # additional upstream IDs as needed
  preconditions:
    - "Environment: <<in-process | test-containers (Postgres 16, Kafka 3.6, ...) | shared-staging | production-like>>"
    - "Fixture: <<named fixture>>"
    - "Test double: <<child component>> as <<dummy | stub | spy | mock | fake>>"
                              # Fakes require a paired contract case — see test-double-discipline.md
    - "Seed: <<data fixture>>"
    - "Provider version pinned: <<service>>@<<sha-or-tag>>"   # for contract cases
    - "Clock: <<fixed at TIMESTAMP | advanceable>>"           # when load-bearing
    - "Random seed: <<integer>>"                              # when load-bearing
  steps:
    - "<<step 1: call into the published interface>>"
    - "<<step 2: observe cross-child state>>"
    # Single Act per case — multiple call-and-observe pairs split into separate cases
  expected:
    - "<<observable on child component A: state, return value, emitted event>>"
    - "<<cross-child invariant holds, e.g., 'order of events preserved across boundary'>>"
    # No qualitative phrases — refusal C
  notes: ""                                       # optional; greenfield only
